-No, absolutely not.

14:14.034 --> 14:16.000
-I mean, this is -- inquiring
minds want to know.

14:16.000 --> 14:18.275
-You guys, I'm just getting
to know him myself.

14:18.275 --> 14:22.724
So you'll meet him as soon as I
decide that he's worth meeting.

14:22.724 --> 14:23.758
Okay?

14:23.758 --> 14:25.068
-Okay.

14:25.068 --> 14:28.137
-We're just happy for you.
-Yeah.

14:28.137 --> 14:29.413
-It's been a journey.

14:29.413 --> 14:32.310
-Oh, my God. I know.
I'm ready.

14:32.310 --> 14:34.724
-I know. Look at you.
-She's ready?

14:34.724 --> 14:39.517
-Yeah, well, you know,
if it works out,

14:39.517 --> 14:41.482
you can finally retire
that vibrator.

14:41.482 --> 14:44.241
-Oh, my God.
You have no idea.

14:44.241 --> 14:47.344
I had to take the batteries
out of the my TV remote.

14:47.344 --> 14:49.034
-I will buy you new batteries.

14:50.896 --> 14:53.206
-We're going to get fired.
We're going to get fired.

14:53.206 --> 14:55.827
-Ladies, I love you.

14:55.827 --> 14:57.689
Please don't ever forget that.

14:57.689 --> 15:00.862
-Aw.

15:51.275 --> 15:53.758
-What am I forgetting, Slice?

16:20.517 --> 16:21.793
-Bruce?

16:29.793 --> 16:31.000
-Hi.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.482
-Hi.
-Is that everything?

16:33.482 --> 16:36.068
-Yeah. Just the essentials.
-Wow.

16:36.068 --> 16:40.000
Stunning and pragmatic.
Might as well kill me now.

16:41.655 --> 16:43.413
Thank you.

16:59.172 --> 17:04.758
-Huh? The weirdest
job I've ever had.

17:04.758 --> 17:08.310
You know, I don't -- I don't
think I've ever had a weird job.

17:08.310 --> 17:10.965
My life was pretty dull
growing up.

17:10.965 --> 17:12.551
What about you?

17:12.551 --> 17:15.517
-When I was in college,
I worked for this ceramicist

17:15.517 --> 17:20.379
who had me hand paint the same
fish pattern on all her vases.

17:20.379 --> 17:22.413
So by the end of the summer,

17:22.413 --> 17:24.206
I'd done it like
a thousand times.

17:24.206 --> 17:25.448
-What kind of fish?

17:25.448 --> 17:29.068
-I'm not sure.
It looked like this.

17:31.034 --> 17:33.103
-Cute.
-Yeah.

17:33.103 --> 17:34.655
-What did you study in school?

17:34.655 --> 17:38.379
-My thesis was on deconstructing
the myth of the muse

17:38.379 --> 17:42.275
and the erasure
of female artists.

17:43.689 --> 17:45.482
-Oh.

17:48.241 --> 17:52.448
-What's the longest relationship
you've ever been in?

17:52.448 --> 17:54.275
-A year.

17:54.275 --> 17:57.931
What about you? What was our
longest relationship?

17:57.931 --> 18:01.241
-Three years.
But it felt like a lot longer.

18:01.241 --> 18:03.793
-Three years?
That sounds kind of serious.

18:03.793 --> 18:05.655
-Yeah.
-Did it end well?

18:05.655 --> 18:09.896
-No. Nope.
He wasn't very nice to me.

18:09.896 --> 18:11.758
-Oh.

18:11.758 --> 18:13.586
Sorry.

18:19.931 --> 18:23.000
But, um, what about your family?

18:23.000 --> 18:25.275
Are you close with your parents?

18:31.206 --> 18:33.689
-They died when I was a kid.

18:34.931 --> 18:38.137
-I'm so sorry. I had no idea.

18:42.724 --> 18:44.172
-How could you?

18:44.172 --> 18:46.655
We're just getting
to know each other.

18:50.413 --> 18:52.344
-Right.

19:20.896 --> 19:22.379
Oh, look at that.

19:22.379 --> 19:24.206
